'''Édgar Yoel Bárcenas Herrera''' (born 23 October 1993) is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Colón, Panama|Colón]], Bárcenas made his senior debut with hometown side [[C.D. Árabe Unido|Árabe Unido]] on 29 July 2012, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 2–2 away draw against [[C.D. Plaza Amador|Plaza Amador]]. He scored his first goal for the club on 1 February 2014, netting the game's only in a home defeat of [[San Francisco F.C.|San Francisco]].

On 15 January 2016, Bárcenas was loaned to Croatian side [[RNK Split]] for six months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.midiario.com/uhora/deportivas/Arroyo-y-Barcenas-a-conquistar-europa|title=Arroyo y Bárcenas a conquistar Europa|trans-title=Arroyo and Bárcenas to conquer Europe|publisher=Mi Diario|language=es|date=15 January 2016|access-date=18 July 2018}}</ref> After appearing rarely, he returned to Árabe Unido before joining [[Ascenso MX]] side [[Cafetaleros de Tapachula]] on 23 January 2017, also in a temporary deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telemetro.com/deportes/futbol/noticias/Panameno-Edgar-Yoel-Barcenas-Mexico_0_992901470.html|title=Panameño Édgar Yoel Bárcenas jugará en México a préstamo|trans-title=Panamanian Edgar Yoel Bárcenas will play in Mexico on loan|publisher=Telemetro|language=es|date=23 January 2017|access-date=18 July 2018}}</ref>

On 26 December 2017, Bárcenas joined Cafetaleros permanently, with a deal to [[Club Tijuana|Tijuana]] arranged in the following July.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elsiglo.com.pa/deportes/jugador-xolos/24040184|title=Ya es jugador de Xolos|trans-title=Already is a Xolos player|publisher=El Siglo|language=es|date=26 December 2017|access-date=18 July 2018|archive-date=25 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825025617/http://elsiglo.com.pa/deportes/jugador-xolos/24040184|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 18 July 2018, however, he was loaned to [[Segunda División]] side [[Real Oviedo]] for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realoviedo.es/noticia/yoel-barcenas-nuevo-jugador-del-real-oviedo|title=Yoel Bárcenas, nuevo jugador del Real Oviedo|trans-title=Yoel Bárcenas, new player of Real Oviedo|publisher=Real Oviedo|language=es|date=18 July 2018|access-date=18 July 2018}}</ref> On 9 August 2019, Bárcenas' loan was extended for a further campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realoviedo.es/noticia/yoel-barcenas-seguira-siendo-oviedista|title=Yoel Bárcenas seguirá siendo oviedista|trans-title=Yoel Bárcenas will remain as an ''oviedista''|publisher=Real Oviedo|language=es|date=9 August 2019|accessdate=14 August 2019}}</ref>

On 5 October 2020, Bárcenas joined [[Girona FC|Girona]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gironafc.cat/noticia/lextrem-yoel-barcenas-reforc-per-a-latac-del-girona|title=L'extrem Yoel Bárcenas, reforç per a l'atac del Girona|trans-title=The winger Yoel Bárcenas reinforces Girona's attack|publisher=Girona FC|language=es|date=5 October 2020|access-date=5 October 2020}}</ref> The following 8 August, he moved to fellow second division team [[CD Leganés]] also in a temporary deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdleganes.com/noticia/el-c-d-leganes-incorpora-a-yoel-barcenas-para-su-frente-de-ataque|title=El C.D. Leganés incorpora a Yoel Bárcenas para su frente de ataque|trans-title=C.D. Leganés sign Yoel Bárcenas for their front lines|publisher=CD Leganés|language=es|date=8 August 2021|access-date=8 August 2021}}</ref>

In June 2022 [[Liga MX]] club [[Mazatlán F.C.|Mazatlán]] announced they had signed Bárcenas to a deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prensa.com/deportes/el-panameno-yoel-barcenas-ficha-por-el-mazatlan-de-mexico/|date=June 25, 2022|work=La Prensa|title=El panameño Edgar Yoel Bárcenas ficha por el Mazatlán de México}}</ref>

==International career==
Bárcenas made his full international debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] on 6 August 2014, in a 3–0 loss against [[Peru national football team|Peru]]. After featuring for [[Panama national under-23 football team|under-23]] side in the [[2015 Pan American Games]], he was included in [[Hernán Darío Gómez]]'s squads for the [[2017 Copa Centroamericana]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/central-american-cup/article/panama-unveils-copa-centroamericana-roster|title=Panama unveils Copa Centroamericana roster|publisher=CONCACAF.com|date=8 January 2017|access-date=18 July 2018}}</ref> and the [[2017 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goldcup.org/en/article/final-23-player-rosters-announced-for-2017-concacaf-gold-cup|title=Final 23-Player Rosters Announced for 2017 CONCACAF Gold Cup|publisher=Gold Cup|date=29 June 2017|access-date=18 July 2018|archive-date=25 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825030138/https://www.goldcup.org/en/article/final-23-player-rosters-announced-for-2017-concacaf-gold-cup|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 14 May 2018, Bárcenas was named in Panama's preliminary 35-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Russia]], and was also among the final squad announced on 30 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fepafut.com/noticias/2116/hernn-daro-gmez-da-listado-de-23-convocados-a-la-copa-mundial|title=Hernán Darío Gómez da listado de 23 convocados a la Copa Mundial|trans-title=Hernán Darío Gómez gives the 23 man called up to the World Cup|publisher=Panamanian Football Federation|language=es|date=30 May 2018|access-date=18 July 2018}}</ref> He appeared in all matches of the tournament, as Panama was knocked out in the group stage.

